<font color="#FF0000">TOWERING  INSULT</font><br>
<tt>Fri Aug  1  0:14:06 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
When the First Cav began to infuse new blood, I guess so that the whole division wouldn't rotate at once, we began to get Cav Vets in our area.  Later, units began to arrive. It seems that they always had this driving need to paint the 1st Cav Div. patch on every water tower in Viet Nam or any other structure over two feet tall.<br>
We anticipated their comming and laid claim to one water tower.  On it we painted, &quot;KEEP AMERICA BEAUTIFUL - STERILIZE THE FIRST CAVALRY!&quot;<br><br>
Since the majority of my flight class had been assigned to the 1st Cav.  I found that sign to be particularily funny.
